        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 7 at 2:52PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 252 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles northwest of Ocate, or 23 miles northeast of Mora, moving
southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ocate.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
